-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Eshraq Properties, Saudi Arabian Mining
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-02-22T13:21:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/persian-gulf-stocks-etisalat-eshraq-properties-are-active.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  gained 0.8
percent to 1,608.92, the highest level since May 4, at the 2
p.m. close in the emirate.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  rose
0.3 percent, while  Saudi Arabia ’s Tadawul All Share Index
climbed 0.9 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Eshraq Properties Co. (ESHRAQ)  (ESHRAQ UH) advanced 10 percent to 33
fils, the highest close since Nov. 13. The board of the Abu
Dhabi-based real-estate developer approved a 2011 dividend of 6
fils a share.  Saudi Arabian Mining Co. (MAADEN)   rose to the highest
since it started trading in July 2008, gaining 1 percent to
30.60 riyals. The state-controlled company known as Maaden will
ask shareholders to authorize the board to sell bonds locally
and abroad.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
